resources.string: Nearly 50 percent of the millionaires got out bed at least three hours before their working actually started. Many of them use the free time to tackle personal projects, plan their day, or make time for exercise. "Getting up at five in the morning to tackle the top three things you want to accomplish in your day allows you to regain control of your life, " he writes. "It give you a sense of confidence that you, indeed, direct your life.
